fact.io.hdureader.zfits

Class ByteWiseHuffmanTree

  • java.lang.Object
    • fact.io.hdureader.zfits.ByteWiseHuffmanTree

  • public class ByteWiseHuffmanTree
extends Object
    A thing I call a ByteWiseHuffmann tree. Each nodes has up to 256 children. This works because the huffmann codes in the zfits files are aligned to bytes. So once a codeword is longer than one byte we traverse down a level. Each leaf contains a ByteWiseTree.Symbol object
    See Also:

    This implementation is quite similar to the things T Bretz and M Bulinski did.

    Created by mackaiver on 16/11/16.
